	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Mockups of games from other platforms</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've compiled a <a href="http://pineight.com/mw/index.php?title=Dot_clock_rates" class="postlink">list of other platforms' dot clock rates</a>. Both the SMS VDP and the NES PPU use the TMS9918 dot clock rate, which is 3/2 of the NTSC colorburst rate. This means the width of active picture is the same for both platforms, but the side-to-side positioning may differ slightly for a couple trivial reasons.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


