		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Practically all Master System games that scroll horizontally mask the leftmost column (8 pixels) so take that into account. Note that the NES can do exactly the same though, so really just do the same thing and forget about it =P<br /><br />Also I was under the impression that the leftmost and rightmost <em>two</em> columns (i.e. 16 pixels each) were not safe. Then again, I'm going by Sega docs, but since the NES screen has the same width and resolution I assume it'd be the same.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
